04/11/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Senate ratified the bilateral treaty of friendship and co-operation with Russia on Monday (3 November), thus completing parliamentary approval of the key political document. Addressing lawmakers, Foreign Minister Mircea Geoana described the treaty as a "balanced" one. The document was sealed in early July, when Romanian President Ion Iliescu visited Moscow. (ACT Media - 04/11/03; Rompres, BBC - 03/11/03)
